{"title":"Circus","author":{"name":"Adam Zagajewski"},"publishDate":"2016-03-30","lines":[{"line":"Look, your longing swung from the trapeze.","stanza":1,"number":1},{"line":"The clown is you as well and the tame tiger","stanza":1,"number":2},{"line":"who begs for mercy calls someone to mind.","stanza":1,"number":3},{"line":"Even the tin-pot music","stanza":1,"number":4},{"line":"has its charm; it seems","stanza":1,"number":5},{"line":"you’re starting to make peace","stanza":1,"number":6},{"line":"with your times (everyone else has,","stanza":1,"number":7},{"line":"why not me?—you say).","stanza":1,"number":8},{"line":"So why then does the circus tent","stanza":1,"number":9},{"line":"rise above an ancient graveyard?","stanza":1,"number":10}]}